race.comment: SUBTERRAIN (5) was well found when facing the starter for the first time but just ran into a couple better in a harder contest in town. Will have taken a lot from that day at the races and can improve enough to take this out. MEADOWBROOK (9) has hit the frame in both career outings to date and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Has plenty of upside and expected to go well. LAAN (8) trialled before racing and then overcame difficulties in running to finish fourth on debut over 1200m at Toowoomba. Will take valuable race experience from that outing and can give this a shake. VAN DE BAN (14) resumed last start and was beaten 4.5 lengths over 1350m at Doomben. Fitter and in the mix.
